headline: Tech rental subscription service Raylo clicks on £30m fundraising
summary: A consumer tech rental service which has struck partnerships with Apple, Dyson and Sony's PlayStation brand has landed £30m in new financial backing and an alliance with LG, the Korean electronics giant.  Sky News has learnt that Raylo, which was founded in 2018, will announce on Tuesday that the American financial services giant Citibank has become a shareholder in the business.  Citibank has led a £10m equity injection in the business, while Raylo has also secured an additional £20m of debt financing from NatWest Group, the high street lender.

Rohit Kulkarni raised his price target on  Amazon  stock to $295 from $270, which implies a 23% increase from the stock’s previous closing price of $239.16.  Kulkarni also maintained a Buy rating on the stock and wrote in a research note on Monday that Amazon is his top mega cap pick for 2026.
